        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(auth): cooldown inline api key billing failures",
        "body": "## Summary\n- track provider-level usage/backoff state for inline `models.providers.<id>.apiKey` credentials without creating synthetic auth profiles\n- skip temporarily disabled inline API keys during auth resolution and availability checks\n- mark inline API keys on provider auth/billing failures so repeated 402s do not immediately retry the same exhausted key\n\nCloses #39807.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n- **Behavior addressed**: Inline `models.providers.<id>.apiKey` credentials now record provider auth/billing failures in usage state, stop immediate reuse during cooldown, and become available again after the cooldown expires without creating a synthetic auth profile.\n- **Environment tested**: Local Linux workstation on PR branch `fix/inline-api-key-billing-cooldown` at `61ac6e93eac913fee891d3d63262518e08185c9d`, using Node/tsx against the production auth profile store, usage helpers, and model auth resolution helpers.\n- **Steps run after the patch**: Ran a Node terminal probe that created a temporary agent directory, configured a dummy inline provider API key, resolved availability before failure, called `markInlineProviderApiKeyFailure(...)` with reason `billing`, checked availability/resolution during cooldown, then simulated cooldown expiry and resolved the inline key again.\n- **Evidence**:\n\n```text\n[agent/embedded] auth profile failure state updated: runId=real-proof-inline-billing profile=sha256:f68577404b84 provider=demo-local reason=billing window=disabled reused=false\n{\n  \"behavior\": \"inline provider apiKey billing failure disables only that inline key and blocks immediate reuse\",\n  \"beforeFailure\": {\n    \"hasAvailableAuth\": true,\n    \"resolvedMode\": \"api-key\",\n    \"resolvedSource\": \"models.json\"\n  },\n  \"recordedFailure\": {\n    \"usageId\": \"inline-api-key:demo-local\",\n    \"profileCreated\": false,\n    \"disabledReason\": \"billing\",\n    \"disabledUntilIsFuture\": true\n  },\n  \"duringCooldown\": {\n    \"hasAvailableAuth\": false,\n    \"blocked\": true,\n    \"blockedMessage\": \"Inline API key for provider \\\"demo-local\\\" is temporarily disabled after a provider auth/billing failure. Retry after about 300 minutes, or switch to a different auth profile/API key.\"\n  },\n  \"afterCooldownExpiry\": {\n    \"hasAvailableAuth\": true,\n    \"resolvedMode\": \"api-key\",\n    \"resolvedSource\": \"models.json\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n- **Observed result**: Before the billing failure, the inline key is available and resolves from `models.json`. After `markInlineProviderApiKeyFailure(...)`, `usageStats[\"inline-api-key:demo-local\"]` records `disabledReason: \"billing\"`, `disabledUntil` is in the future, no synthetic profile is created, `hasAvailableAuthForProvider(...)` returns false, and `resolveApiKeyForProvider(...)` blocks immediate reuse with the temporary-disabled error. After simulated cooldown expiry, the same inline key becomes available and resolves from `models.json` again.\n- **Not tested**: A live paid provider 402 against a real provider account; this avoids intentionally causing a real billing failure while still exercising the production failure-marking and auth-resolution path with a redacted dummy inline key.\n\n## Validation\n- `pnpm test src/agents/auth-profiles.markauthprofilefailure.test.ts src/agents/model-auth.profiles.test.ts` (2 files, 66 tests passed)\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 src/agents/auth-profiles/usage.ts src/agents/auth-profiles.ts src/agents/model-auth.ts src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/run.ts src/agents/auth-profiles.markauthprofilefailure.test.ts src/agents/model-auth.profiles.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check`\n\n## Additional real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior addressed after review**: the actual embedded-runner failure paths now call the inline provider API-key marker even when the active credential has no profile id.\n- **Environment tested**: local checkout after merging upstream/main into fix/inline-api-key-billing-cooldown at ce378baab4.\n- **Evidence after fix**: added runner-path coverage that simulates an inline models.providers.openai.apiKey billing failure with no auth profile and verifies auth-state.json records inline-api-key:openai with disabledReason: \"billing\" and a future disabledUntil.\n- **Validation after fix**:\n  - ./node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check --threads=1 src/agents/auth-profiles/usage.ts src/agents/auth-profiles.ts src/agents/model-auth.ts src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/run.ts src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/run/assistant-failover.ts src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/run/assistant-failover.test.ts src/agents/pi-embedded-runner.run-embedded-pi-agent.auth-profile-rotation.e2e.test.ts src/agents/auth-profiles.markauthprofilefailure.test.ts src/agents/model-auth.profiles.test.ts\n  - git diff --check\n  - ./node_modules/.bin/vitest run src/agents/auth-profiles.markauthprofilefailure.test.ts src/agents/model-auth.profiles.test.ts src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/run/assistant-failover.test.ts src/agents/pi-embedded-runner.run-embedded-pi-agent.auth-profile-rotation.e2e.test.ts --reporter=dot — 6 files, 156 tests passed.\n",
        "branch": "fix/inline-api-key-billing-cooldown",
